Weights preloaded
Accumulators local
Data streams through
So real designs often combine strategies.


✅ Project plan clarification

➡️ For the first version of this project:
We will implement output-stationary, because it’s the simplest:
Accumulator stays in PE
A & B both stream
I suggested weight-stationary as an optional second mode, but to avoid confusion:
✅ We will build output-stationary first, not weight-stationary.
Why?
Output-stationary is the standard intro GEMM systolic array
Easier to understand + verify
Many open-source examples follow this
Avoids storing B in PE
So:
✅ First: Output-stationary
Optional later: Add weight-stationary mode

